<br>
I found this on one of the boards. This is good to know for everyone when we fight major mobs like giants and such.<br>
<br>
Flurry: extra set of attack per round. Will only affect your MT.<br>
<br>
Enrage: Mobs that are melee type will enrage, ie, autoriposte all your frontal hits. It's fine if you attack from back but watch for turning mobs or you'll be puree.<br>
<br>
Rampage: Mob will do an attack round on one extra person other than MT. I'm sure there will be 20 people that will say rampage hit 5 more targets, but that's because the rampage people keep dying. It's really 1 more person. Depending on the encounters, you will have to learn how to deal with it. It can go from healing the small damage (Vindicator rampages rarely, for example) to other strategies (Arch Lich rampages every round). The fun part is figuring the boss mob fights.<br>
<br>
Rampages from non-boss mobs can be disregarded with small healing from druids and such.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291503"Target=_blank">Soluafein</a>
<br>
